-- Indian Oil to Add as Many as 800 Retail Outlets, Financial Chronicle Says
-- Abhishek Shanker
-- 2010-07-06T02:13:47Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-06/indian-oil-to-add-as-many-as-800-retail-outlets-financial-chronicle-says.html

          
          
             Indian Oil Corp., the country’s
biggest state refiner, will add up to 800 retail outlets in a
year in rural and semi-urban locations, the Financial Chronicle
reported today, citing a company official it didn’t identify.  
 To contact the reporter on this story:
